      • crawlIn

        public void crawlIn(int thiefId)
        In the Ordinary Thief life cycle, transition between "crawling inwards" and "crawling inwards". Method to signal a Thief to crawl inwards a room. Each thief has to wait while it is not his time to crawl. Each thief only crawls one position, wakes up the next thief to crawl and then sleeps. This happen until all the thieves have arrived to the room. Same process implemented on crawlOut method.
        Specified by:

      • crawlOut

        public void crawlOut(int thiefId)
        In the Ordinary Thief life cycle, transition between "crawling outwards" and "crawling outwards". Method to signal a Thief to crawl outwards outside. Each thief has to wait while it is not his time to crawl. Each thief only crawls one position, wakes up the next thief to crawl and then sleeps. This happen until all the thieves have arrived to the outside. Same process implemented on crawlIn method.
